<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-02-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="288" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d288">
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                                </head>
                                <p>No official record of this conversation has been found. According
                                    to the account in Pickersgill, p. 416, from which the
                                    information above has been derived, the subject of the
                                    conversation was Canada’s desire for representation on the
                                    Combined Munitions Assignment Board.</p>
